				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">MegaCD could be powered from the MD side, but only on models that do not have carbon covered contacts on the expansion connector... all japanese units have carbon coated connections. Those few ohms of resistance the carbon causes is enough to cause instability when the MCD is powered from MD during seeking operations when power draw is greatest.<br />Scraping off the carbon would fix the problem and that is what I do on my machines to make them behave good on my &quot;single AC brick modded&quot; MegaCD.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.tmeeco.eu">http://www.tmeeco.eu</a><!-- m --></div>
